From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 16:32:43 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 146/174] =?UTF-8?q?mm:=20PGCL=20=E2=80=94=20remove=20corru?=
 =?UTF-8?q?ption-detector=20maskers=20(restore=20mainline=20checks)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The PGCL series had carried two band-aids that SILENCE the kernel's own
corruption detectors instead of fixing the conditions that trip them:

  - mm/swap.c __page_cache_release(): an else-branch that unconditionally
    cleared PG_active/PG_unevictable on the non-LRU free path "to prevent
    free_page_is_bad() from firing".
  - mm/memory.c zap_present_folio_ptes(): dropped mainline's
    `if (folio_mapcount(folio) < 0) print_bad_pte(...)` negative-mapcount
    check after folio_remove_rmap_ptes().

Both are upstream-unacceptable (no reviewer takes a series that quiets
free_page_is_bad / print_bad_pte rather than fixing why a bad page is freed
or why a mapcount went negative) and both blinded our own test matrix to the
corrupt-free / bad-mapcount classes.

Remove them.  Each restores the exact mainline code, so this is byte-identical
to mainline at PAGE_MMUSHIFT==0 (Newton limit) and simply re-arms the
detectors at PAGE_MMUSHIFT>0.  The cheap x86_64 PGCL=0/4 tier already runs
clean with both removed (LTP 71p/0f/28s, no free_page_is_bad, no
print_bad_pte); a per-arch un-silenced sweep follows to surface anything else
that was masked.  Compile-verified x86_64 at PAGE_MMUSHIFT=0 and =4.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 mm/memory.c |  6 +++++-
 mm/swap.c   | 10 ----------
 2 files changed, 5 insertions(+), 11 deletions(-)

diff --git a/mm/memory.c b/mm/memory.c
index 7014e75e60b2..17a97029c95d 100644
--- a/mm/memory.c
+++ b/mm/memory.c
@@ -1756,8 +1756,12 @@ static __always_inline void zap_present_folio_ptes(struct mmu_gather *tlb,
 		*any_skipped = zap_install_uffd_wp_if_needed(vma, addr, pte,
 							     nr, details, ptent);
 
-	if (!delay_rmap)
+	if (!delay_rmap) {
 		folio_remove_rmap_ptes(folio, page, nr, vma);
+
+		if (unlikely(folio_mapcount(folio) < 0))
+			print_bad_pte(vma, addr, ptent, page);
+	}
 	if (unlikely(__tlb_remove_folio_pages(tlb, page, nr, delay_rmap))) {
 		*force_flush = true;
 		*force_break = true;
diff --git a/mm/swap.c b/mm/swap.c
index c322c66f4195..5cc44f0de987 100644
--- a/mm/swap.c
+++ b/mm/swap.c
@@ -77,16 +77,6 @@ static void __page_cache_release(struct folio *folio, struct lruvec **lruvecp,
 		folio_lruvec_relock_irqsave(folio, lruvecp, flagsp);
 		lruvec_del_folio(*lruvecp, folio);
 		__folio_clear_lru_flags(folio);
-	} else {
-		/*
-		 * MGLRU may isolate a folio (clearing PG_lru) and set
-		 * PG_active before the folio is freed.  Clear these flags
-		 * unconditionally to prevent free_page_is_bad() from firing.
-		 */
-		if (folio_test_active(folio))
-			__folio_clear_active(folio);
-		if (folio_test_unevictable(folio))
-			__folio_clear_unevictable(folio);
 	}
 }
 
